-- U.K. Stocks Rally After Spain Sells Debt; FTSE 100 Gains 0.5%
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2012-01-12T09:57:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/u-k-stocks-rally-after-spain-sells-debt-ftse-100-gains-0-5-.html
U.K. stocks climbed after  Spain 
sold 9.98 billion euros of government bonds at an auction today,
almost double the 5 billion-euro target.  The FTSE 100 Index climbed 0.5 percent to 5,698.23 at 9:56
a.m. in  London . The gauge fell 0.2 percent earlier.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
